<div class='layout'><p>"Yes,……I still want a knife."</p><p>“没错，但我仍想要一把刀。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He said, "Its against……law to sell knives."</p><p>他说：“卖刀是违法的。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "I'm……a policewoman or a government agent of……sort.……going to Billibotton."</p><p>铎丝说：“我不是女警，也不是任何一种政府特务。我是要到脐眼去。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He stared at……thoughtfully. "Alone?"</p><p>他意味深长地瞪着她。“一个人？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"With my friend."……jerked……thumb over……shoulder in……direction of Seldon,……was waiting outside sullenly.</p><p>“和我的朋友一起。”她将拇指朝肩后一甩，指向谢顿的方向，他正绷着脸等在外面。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Youre buying it……him?" He stared at Seldon……it didnt take……long to decide. "Hes an outsider too.……him come in……buy it……himself."</p><p>“你是要帮他买？”他瞪了谢顿一眼，很快便做出判断。“他也是个外人，让他自己进来买。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Hes……a government agent either.……I'm buying it……myself."</p><p>“他也不是政府特务，而且我买刀是给自己用。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The dealer shook……head. "Outsiders……crazy.……if……want to spend some credits, I'll take them from you."</p><p>老板摇了摇头。“外人可都很疯狂。但你若想花掉些信用点，我不介意从你手中接过来。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He reached under……counter, brought……a stub, turned it with a slight……expert motion,……the knife blade emerged.</p><p>他从柜台下面掏出一根粗短的圆棒，再以行家的动作轻轻一转，刀锋便立刻冒出来。</p></div>
