<div class='layout'><p>The dealer obliged.</p><p>老板遵命照办。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "All right, close it……toss me……haft."</p><p>铎丝说：“好啦，收起来，再把刀柄丢给我。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He did, in a slow upward loop.</p><p>他依言照做，刀子缓缓画出一道弧线。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She caught……handed it back,……said, "Faster."</p><p>她接住后又还了回去，并且说：“快一点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He raised……eyebrows……then, without warning, backhanded it to……left side.……made no attempt to bring over……right hand,……caught it with……left……the blade showed tumescently at once--then disappeared.……dealers mouth fell open.</p><p>老板扬起眉毛，然后在毫无预警的情况下，反手将刀丢向她的左侧。她并未试图伸出右手，而是直接用左手接住。刀锋立刻冒出头来，下一刻又随即消失。老板看得张口结舌。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"And this is……largest……have?"……said.</p><p>“这是你店里最大的一款？”她问道。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It……If……try to……it, it Will just tire……out."</p><p>“是的。你若试图用这把刀，必会令你筋疲力尽。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'll breathe deeply. I'll take a second……too."</p><p>“我会多做深呼吸。我还要一把。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"For your friend?"</p><p>“给你的朋友？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No.……me."</p><p>“不，给我自己。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You plan on using……knives?"</p><p>“你打算使双刀？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Ive……two hands."</p><p>“我有两只手。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The dealer sighed. "Mistress, please stay……of Billibotton.……don't know what they do to women there."</p><p>老板叹了一声。“夫人，奉劝你离脐眼远一点。你不知道他们那里怎样对付女人。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I……guess.……do I……these knives on my belt?"</p><p>“我猜得到。我该怎样将这两把刀插进皮带里？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Not……one youve……on, Mistress. Thats……a knife belt. I……sell……one, though."</p><p>“夫人，你身上那条皮带不行，那不是刀带。不过，我可以卖一条给你。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Will it hold……knives?"</p><p>“能装两把刀吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I might have a double belt somewhere.……much call……them."</p><p>“我应该还有一条双刀带，它们的需求量不大。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'm calling……them."</p><p>“我现在就有需求。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I……not have it in your size."</p><p>“我也许没有你要的尺寸。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Then well……it down or something."</p><p>“我们会把它切短，或是想别的办法。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It Will cost……a……of credits."</p><p>“你得付出许多信用点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"My credit tile Will cover it."</p><p>“我的信用瓷卡付得起。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>When……emerged at last, Seldon said sourly, "You look ridiculous with that bulky belt."</p><p>等到她终于走出来，谢顿以酸酸的口气说：“这条笨重的皮带令你看来真滑稽。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Really, Hari?……ridiculous to go with……to Billibotton? Then lets both go back to……apartment."</p><p>“真的吗，哈里？是不是太滑稽了，不配跟你到脐眼去？那我们就一同回公寓吧。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No. I'll go on by myself. I'll be safer by myself."</p><p>“不，我要自己去。我自己去会比较安全。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "There is no……saying that, Hari. We both go back or we both go forward. Under no circumstances do we separate."</p><p>铎丝说：“哈里，这样说一点用也没有。让我们一起向后转，否则就一起向前走。不论在任何情况下，我们都不会分开。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And somehow……firm look in……blue eyes,……set to……lips,……the manner in which……hands……dropped to……hafts at……belt, convinced Seldon……was serious.</p><p>此时，她的蓝眼珠所透出的坚决眼神，她的嘴角所弯成的弧度，以及她双手放在腰际刀柄上的姿势，在在使谢顿相信她是认真的。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Very well," he said, "but if……survive……if I ever……Hummin again, my price……continuing to work on psychohistory--much as I have grown fond of you--Will be your removal. Do……understand?"</p><p>“很好，”他说，“但如果你活着回来，又如果我还能见到夫铭，那么，要我继续研究心理史学的条件就是让你消失——虽然我越来越喜欢你。你能了解吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And suddenly Dors smiled. "Forget……don't practice your chivalry on……Nothing Will remove……Do……understand?"</p><p>铎丝突然露出微笑。“忘掉这码事吧，别把你的骑士精神用在我身上。无论如何我都不会消失的，你能了解吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>They……off……Expressway where……sign, flickering in……air, said: BILLIBOTTON. As perhaps an indication of what might be expected,……second I……smeared, a mere blob of fainter light.</p><p>看到“脐眼”这个路标在半空闪烁，他们两人便下了捷运。路标第一个字左侧污损了，只剩下一个黯淡的光点，这也许正意味着这是个什么样的环境。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>They made their……out of……car……down to……walkway below. It……early afternoon……at first glance, Billibotton seemed much like……part of Dahl they……left.</p><p>走出车厢之后，他们沿着下面的人行道前进。此时刚过正午，乍看之下，脐眼似乎很像他们居住的那一带达尔区。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The air, however,……a pungent aroma……the walkway……littered with trash.</p><p>然而，空气中有一种刺激性的气味，人行道处处可见乱丢的垃圾。由此即可看出，附近绝对见不到自动扫街器。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>One could tell that auto-sweeps were……to be found in……neighborhood. And, although……walkway looked ordinary enough,……atmosphere……uncomfortable……as tense as a too-tightly coiled spring. </p><p>此外，虽然人行道看来相当普通，此地的气氛却令人很不舒服，有如扭得太紧的弹簧那般紧绷。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Perhaps it……the people. There seemed……normal number of pedestrians,……they were……like pedestrians elsewhere, Seldon thought. Ordinarily, in……press of business, pedestrians were self-absorbed……in……endless crowds on……endless thoroughfares of Trantor, people could only survive--psychologically--by ignoring each other. Eyes slid away. Brains were closed off. There……an artificial privacy with each person enclosed in a velvet……of……or……own making. Or there……the ritualistic friendliness of an evening promenade in those neighborhoods that indulged in such things.</p><p>或许是因为人的关系。行人的数目似乎还算正常，但谢顿心想，他们却和其他地方的行人不一样。通常，在工作压力下，每个行人心中都只有自己；置身川陀无数大街小巷的无数人群中，就心理层面而言，人们唯有忽略他人才能活下去。例如目光绝不流连，大脑完全封闭。人人罩在一团自制的浓雾里，也能获得一种人工的隐私。反之，在那些热衷于黄昏漫步的社区中，则充满一种仪式化的亲切感。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>……here in Billibotton, there……neither friendliness……neutral withdrawal. At least……where outsiders were concerned. Every person……passed, moving in either direction, turned to stare at Seldon……Dors. Every pair of eyes, as though attached by invisible cords to……two outsiders, followed them with I'll will.</p><p>但在脐眼这里，至少对外人而言，却是既没有亲切感也没有漠然的回避。每个擦身而过的人，不论是来是往，都会转头朝谢顿与铎丝瞪上一眼。每对眼睛仿佛都有隐形绳索系在这两个外人身上，带着恶意紧追着他们不放。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The clothing of……Billibottoners tended to be smudged, old,……sometimes corn. There……a patina of ill-washed poverty over them……Seldon felt uneasy at……slickness of……own……clothes.</p><p>脐眼人的衣着较为肮脏和老旧，有些还已经破损。这些衣服都带着一种没洗干净的晦暗，令谢顿不禁对自己光鲜的新衣感到不安。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He said, "Where in Billibotton does Mother Rittah live, do……suppose?"</p><p>他说：“照你想来，瑞塔嬷嬷会住在脐眼哪里？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't know," said Dors. "You brought us here, so……do……supposing. I intend to confine myself to……task of protection……I think……going to find it necessary to do just that."</p><p>“我不知道。”铎丝说，“你把我俩带到这里，所以应该由你来想。我打算专注于保镖的工作，我想我会发现确有必要只做这一件事。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, "I assumed it would only be necessary to……the……of……passerby,……somehow……not encouraged to do so."</p><p>谢顿说：“而我认为确有必要随便找个路人问问，但我又不太想这么做。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I don't blame you. I don't think youll find anyone springing to your assistance."</p><p>“我不会怪你的，我也认为你找不到任何愿意帮助你的热心人士。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"On……other hand, there……such things as youngsters." He indicated……with a brief gesture of……hand. A……who looked to be about twelve--in……case young enough to lack……universal adult male mustache……come to a full halt……was staring at them.</p><p>“话说回来，别忘了还有少年这种东西。”谢顿随手指了指其中一个。那个男孩看来大约十二岁，总之尚未蓄起成年男子不可或缺的八字胡。他已停下脚步，正盯着他们两人。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Youre guessing that a……that……has……yet developed……full Billibottonian dislike of outsiders."</p><p>铎丝说：“你是在猜想，那种年纪的男孩尚未完全发展出脐眼人对外人的厌恶。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"At……rate," said Seldon, "I'm guessing he is scarcely large enough to have developed……full Billibottonian penchant……violence. I suppose he might……away……shout insults from a distance if we approach him,……I doubt hell attack us."</p><p>“至少，”谢顿说，“我猜想他的年纪还小，不至于完全发展出脐眼的暴力倾向。我想如果我们走近他，他可能会拔腿就跑，在老远的地方高声辱骂，但我不信他会攻击我们。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon raised……voice. "Young man."</p><p>谢顿提高音量说：“年轻人。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……took a step backward……continued to stare.</p><p>男孩向后退了一步，继续瞪着他们两人。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, "Come here,"……beckoned.</p><p>谢顿说：“到这里来。”同时招了招手。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……said,……for, guy?"</p><p>男孩说：“哥儿们，干啥？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"So I……ask……directions. Come closer, so I don't have to shout."</p><p>“好让我能向你问路。走近一点，好让我不必大吼大叫。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……approached……steps closer.……face……smudged,……his eyes were bright……sharp.……sandals were of different make……there……a large patch on……leg of……trousers.</p><p>男孩向前走了两步。他的脸孔脏兮兮，一双眼睛却明亮而敏锐。他的凉鞋式样与众不同，短裤的一侧还有个大补丁。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He said,……kind o directions?"</p><p>他说：“啥样的路？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Were trying to find Mother Rittah."</p><p>“我们想要找瑞塔嬷嬷。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The boys eyes flickered.……for, guy?"</p><p>男孩的眼睛亮了起来。“哥儿们，干啥？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'm a scholar. Do……know what a scholar is?"</p><p>“我是一名学者。你知道学者是什么吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Ya went to school?"</p><p>“你上过学？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Yes. Didnt you?"</p><p>“没错。你没有吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……spat to……side in contempt. "Nah."</p><p>男孩不屑地向一旁啐了一口。“没。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I want advice from Mother Rittah--if youll take me to her."</p><p>“我有事要请教瑞塔嬷嬷，希望你能带我去找她。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Ya want your fortune? Ya come to Billibotton, guy, with your fancy clothes, so I……tell ya your fortune.……bad."</p><p>“你要算命？哥儿们，你穿着拉风的衣服来脐眼，连我都能帮你算命——霉运当头。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Whats your name, young man?"</p><p>“年轻人，你叫什么名字？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Whats it to ya?"</p><p>“跟你何干？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"So we……speak in a more friendly fashion.……so……can take me to Mother Rittahs place. Do……know where……lives?"</p><p>“好让我们能以更友善的方式交谈，好让你可以带我去瑞塔嬷嬷的住处。你知道她住在哪里吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Maybe yes, maybe……My names Raych. Whats in it……me if I take ya?"</p><p>“也许知，也许不知。我叫芮奇，如果我带你去，有什么好处？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What would……like, Raych?"</p><p>“芮奇，你想要什么？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The boys eyes halted at Dorss belt. Raych said, "The lady……a couple o knives. Gimme……and I'll take ya to Mother Rittah."</p><p>男孩的目光停留在铎丝的腰带上，他说：“这大姐带着双刀。给我一把，我就带你去找瑞塔嬷嬷。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Those……grown peoples knives, Raych. Youre……young."</p><p>“那是成人用的刀，芮奇，你的年纪还太小。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Then I guess……too young to know where Mother Rittah lives."……he looked up slyly through……shaggy halt that curtained……eyes.</p><p>“那么我猜我的年纪也太小，不会知道瑞塔嬷嬷住在哪里。”说完他抬起头，透过遮住眼睛的乱发狡猾地望向对方。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon grew uneasy. It……possible they might attract a crowd. Several……had stopped already,……had then moved on when nothing of interest seemed to be taking place.……however,……boy grew angry……lashed……at them in word or deed, people would undoubtedly gather.</p><p>谢顿开始感到不安，再这样下去，可能会引来一群人。已经有几名男子停下来，但在发现似乎没有什么看头之后，他们又全都掉头离去。然而，倘若这个男孩发起脾气，以言语或行动攻击他们，路人无疑会群聚过来。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He smiled……said, "Can……read, Raych?"</p><p>他微微一笑。“芮奇，你识字吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raych spat again. "Nah!……wants to read?"</p><p>芮奇又啐了一口。“不！谁要识字？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Can……use a computer?"</p><p>“你会用电脑吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"A talking computer? Sure. Anyone can."</p><p>“会说话的电脑吗？当然，人人都会。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'll tell……what, then.……take me to……nearest computer store……I'll……you a little computer……your……and software that Will teach……to read. A……weeks……youll be able to read."</p><p>“那么，我告诉你怎么办。你带我到最近的一家电脑店，我帮你买一台属于你自己的小电脑，以及一套能教你识字的软件。几个星期后，你就识字了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>It seemed to Seldon that……boys eyes sparkled at……thought, but--if so--they hardened at once. "Nah, Knife or nothin."</p><p>谢顿发觉男孩的眼睛似乎为之一亮，但即便如此，那目光随即又转趋强硬。“不，不给刀子就拉倒。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Thats……point, Raych.……learn to read……don't tell anyone……you……surprise people. After a while……can……them……can read.……them five credits.……can……a……extra credits that……and……can……a knife of your own."</p><p>“芮奇，关键就在这里。你自己学识字，别告诉任何人，就能让大家吃一惊。过一阵子之后，你可以打赌说你会识字，和他们赌五个信用点。这样你就能赢得不少零用钱，就可以帮自己买把刀子。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……hesitated. "Nah! No……Will……me. No……got credits."</p><p>男孩犹豫了一下。“不！没人会和我打赌，没人有信用点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"If……can read,……can……a……in a knife store……you……save your wages……get a knife at a discount.……about that?"</p><p>“只要你识字，就能在刀店找到一份工作。你把工资存起来，就可以用折扣价买一把刀。这样好不好？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"When ya gonna……the talking computer?"</p><p>“你什么时候去买会说话的电脑？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Right now. I'll give it to……when I……Mother Rittah."</p><p>“马上去，但要等我见到瑞塔嬷嬷再给你。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You……credits?"</p><p>“你有信用点？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I have a credit tile."</p><p>“我有信用瓷卡。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Lets……ya……the computer."</p><p>“我们一起去买电脑吧。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The transaction……carried through,……when……boy reached……it, Seldon shook……head……put it inside……pouch. "Youve……to……me to Mother Rittah first, Raych.……you sure……know where to find her?"</p><p>电脑的交易进行得很顺利，但是当男孩伸出手的时候，谢顿却摇了摇头，并将它放进自己的袋囊。“芮奇，你得先带我去找瑞塔嬷嬷。你确定知道能在哪儿找到她吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raych allowed a look of contempt to cross……face. "Sure I……I'll take ya there, only ya better hand over……computer when we……there or I'll……some guys I know after……and……lady, so ya better watch out."</p><p>芮奇刻意流露出不屑的表情。“我当然确定。我会带你到那儿去，只不过我们到了之后，你最好把电脑给我。否则我会找些相熟的哥儿们，去追你和这个大姐，所以你最好小心点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You don't have to threaten us," said Seldon. "Well take care of……end of……deal."</p><p>“你不必威胁我们。”谢顿说，“我们会履行我方的义务。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raych……them quickly along……walkway, past curious stares. </p><p>芮奇带着他们沿人行道快步走去，穿过了许多好奇的目光。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon……silent during……walk……so……Dors. Dors……far less lost in……own thoughts, though,……she clearly remained conscious of……surrounding people at……times.……kept meeting, with a level glare,……eyes of those passersby that turned toward them. On occasion, when there were footsteps behind them,……turned to look grimly back.</p><p>谢顿一路上一言不发，而铎丝也一样。不过相较之下，铎丝并非在想什么心事，她显然一直在警戒着周遭的人群。对于那些转头望向他们的路人，她总是以直勾勾的凶狠眼神接触他们的目光。有好几次，当他们身后传来脚步声时，她都立刻转头怒目而视。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And then Raych stopped……said,……here.……aint homeless, ya know."</p><p>然后芮奇停了下来，说道：“就在这里。你瞧，她不是无家可归。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>They followed……into an apartment complex……Seldon,……had……the intention of following their route with a view to retracing……steps later,……quickly lost.</p><p>他们跟着他进入一组公寓群。谢顿本想在心中默记走过的路线，以便待会儿能自行找到出路，却很快就迷失了方向。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He said, "How do……know your……through these alleys, Raych?"</p><p>他说：“芮奇，你怎么知道这些巷道该走哪一条？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……shrugged. "I been loafin through them since I……a kid," he said. "Besides,……apartments……numbered--where they aint broken off--and theres arrows……things.……cant……lost if……know……tricks."</p><p>男孩耸了耸肩。“打从小时候，我就在这些巷道中游荡。”他说，“而且，这些公寓都有号码——除非脱落——还有箭头和其他东西。只要知道这些窍门，你就不可能迷路。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Raych knew……tricks, apparently,……they wandered deeper into……complex. Hanging over it……was an……of total decay: disregarded debris, inhabitants slinking past in clear resentment of……outsiders invasion. Unruly youngsters……along……alleys in pursuit of some game or other. Some of them yelled, "Hey,……out o……way!" when their levitating ball narrowly missed Dors. </p><p>芮奇显然深通这些窍门，于是他们逐渐深入公寓群。徘徊不去的是一种完全腐朽的气氛，瓦砾堆无人清理，一闪而过的居民对外人入侵表露出明显恨意。又皮又野的少年沿着巷道奔跑追逐，似乎正在玩某种游戏。当他们的飞球险些击中铎丝时，有些还大叫道：“嘿，让路！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And finally, Raych stopped before a dark scarred door on which……number 2782 glowed feebly.</p><p>最后，芮奇停在一扇斑驳的深色大门之前，门上微微闪着“2782”这组数字。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"This iiiit," he said……held……his hand.</p><p>“这里就是。”他一面说，一面伸出手来。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"First lets……whos inside," said Seldon softly. He pushed……signal button……nothing happened.</p><p>“我们先看看谁在里面。”谢顿轻声道。他按下讯号钮，却没有任何反应。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It don't work," said Raych.……gotta bang. Loud.……don't hear……good."</p><p>“没用。”芮奇说，“你得捶门，捶得很响才行。她的耳朵不太好。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon pounded……fist on……door……was rewarded with……sound of movement inside. A shrill voice called out, "Who wants Mother Rittah?"</p><p>于是谢顿握拳猛击门板，果然听到里面有了动静。一个尖锐的声音传出来：“谁要见瑞塔嬷嬷？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon shouted, "Two scholars!"</p><p>谢顿喊道：“两名学者！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He tossed……small computer, with……small package of software attached, to Raych,……snatchediit, grinned,……took……at a rapid run.Seldon then turned to face……opening door……Mother Rittah.</p><p>他将小电脑连同附带的软件套件一起扔给芮奇，芮奇一把抓住，咧嘴一笑，便快步跑走了。然后谢顿转过头来，面对着打开的门与门后的瑞塔嬷嬷。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Mother Rittah……well into……seventies, perhaps,……had……kind of face that, at first sight, seemed to belie that. Plump cheeks, a little mouth, a small round chin slightly doubled.……was very short--not quite……meters tall--and……a thick body.</p><p>瑞塔嬷嬷或许已有七十好几，但她的脸孔乍看之下似乎没有那么老。她的面颊丰满，嘴巴不大，轻微的双下巴则又小又圆。她个子非常矮——还不到一米五，却有一副粗壮的身躯。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>But there were fine wrinkles about……eyes……when……smiled, as……smiled at……sight of them, others broke……over……face.……she moved with difficulty.</p><p>不过她的双眼周围有着细微的皱纹。每当她微笑的时候，例如见到他们之后的那一笑，脸部其他各处的皱纹也会绽露出来。此外，她的行动有些困难。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Come……come in,"……said in a soft high-pitchedivoice……peered at them as though……eyesight……beginning to fail. "Outsiders……Outworlders even. Am I right?……don't seem to have……Trantor smell about you."</p><p>“进来，进来。”她一面以轻柔高亢的声音这么说，一面眯着眼睛凝视他们两人，仿佛她的视力也开始减退了。“外人……甚至还是外星人士，我说对了吗？你们身上似乎没有川陀的气味。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon wished……hadn't mentioned smell.……apartment, overcrowded……littered with small possessions that seemed dI'm……dusty, reeked with food odors that were on……edge of rancidity.……air……so thick……clinging that he……sure……clothes would smell strongly of it when they left.</p><p>谢顿真希望她未曾提到气味。这间过分拥挤的公寓发出一股食物的怪味，那是一种几乎接近腐臭的味道。屋内还有许多四处乱丢的小东西，都是一些看来陈旧而且盖满灰尘的物品。这里的空气如此浓浊粘稠，他可以确定即使离开这里之后，衣服上仍会带着这种强烈的气味。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He said, "You……right, Mother Rittah. I am Hari Seldon of Helicon. My friend is Dors Venabili of Cinna."</p><p>他说：“瑞塔嬷嬷，你说对了。我是来自赫利肯的哈里·谢顿，我的朋友是来自锡纳的铎丝·凡纳比里。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"So,"……said, looking about……an unoccupied spot on……floor where……could invite them to sit,……finding none suitable.</p><p>“好。”她一面说，一面在地板上寻找一个空位，以便邀请他们坐下，可是却找不到合适的角落。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said,……are willing to stand, Mother."</p><p>铎丝说：“嬷嬷，我们乐意站着。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What?"……looked up at Dors. "You must speak briskly, my child. My hearing is……what it……when I……your age."</p><p>“什么？”她抬起头望着铎丝，“孩子，你说话必须中气十足。我的听力不再像你这个年纪时那么好了。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Why don't……get a hearing device?" said Seldon, raising……voice.</p><p>“你为什么不弄个助听装置？”谢顿提高音量说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It wouldnt help, Master Seldon. Something seems to be wrong with……nerve……I have no money……nerve rebuilding.--You have come to learn……future from……Mother Rittah?"</p><p>“谢顿老爷，那没什么帮助。好像是神经方面的毛病，我却没钱去做神经重建。你们是来向瑞塔老嬷嬷请教未来之事？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Not quite," said Seldon. "I have come to learn……past."</p><p>“并不尽然。”谢顿说，“我是来请教过去之事。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Excellent. It is such a strain to decide what people want to hear."</p><p>“好极了。判断人们想听些什么可不容易。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It must be quite an art," said Dors, smiling.</p><p>“那必定是一门高深的技艺。”铎丝微笑着说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It seems easy,……one……to he properly convincing. I earn my fees."</p><p>“看来容易，可是必须令人心服口服。我就靠它为生。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"If……have a credit outlet," said Seldon.……Will……any reasonable fees if……tell us about Earth--without cleverly designing what……tell us to suit what we want to hear. We wish to hear……truth."</p><p>“如果你有刷卡插座，”谢顿说，“我们会付你合理的酬劳。只要你告诉我们有关地球的事，其中没有为了满足我们而巧妙编织的话语——我们希望听的是事实。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……woman,……had been shuffling about……room, making adjustments here……there, as though to make it……prettier……more suitable……important visitors, stopped short. "What do……want to know about Earth?"</p><p>老妇人本来一直在屋里踱来踱去，东摸摸西弄弄，仿佛要将房间弄得更漂亮，更适合招待两位来访的贵客。此时她忽然停下来，说道：“你要知道有关地球的什么事？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What is……to begin with?"</p><p>“首先，它究竟是什么？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……woman turned……seemed to gaze……into space. When……spoke,……voice……low……steady.</p><p>老妇人转过身来，目光似乎投射到太空中。当她开始说话的时候，她的声音变得又沉又稳。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It is a world, a very……planet. It is forgotten……lost."</p><p>“它是一个世界，是一颗非常古老的行星。它遭人遗忘，如今下落不明。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said,……is……part of history. We know that much."</p><p>铎丝说：“它并非历史的一部分，这点我们还知道。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It comes before history, child," said Mother Rittah solemnly.……existed in……dawn of……Galaxy……before……dawn. It……the only world with humanity."……nodded firmly.</p><p>“孩子，它比历史更为古老。”瑞塔嬷嬷严肃地说，“它存在于银河的黎明期，以及黎明期之前。当时它是唯一拥有人类的世界。”她坚定地点了点头。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, "Was another name……Earth……Aurora?"</p><p>谢顿问道：“地球的别名是不是……奥罗拉？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And……Mother Rittahs face misted into a frown. "Where……you hear that?"</p><p>这时，瑞塔嬷嬷的脸孔突然皱成一团。“这个名字你是从哪里听来的？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"In my wanderings. I have heard of an……forgotten world named Aurora on which humanity lived in primordial peace."</p><p>“在我东闯西荡中。我听说，有个古老而遭人遗忘的世界名叫奥罗拉，上面的人曾经享有太初的平静岁月。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Its a lie."……wiped……mouth as though to……the taste of what……had just heard……of……"That name……mention must never be mentioned except as……place of Evil. It……the beginning of Evil. Earth……alone till Evil came, along with……sister worlds. Evil nearly destroyed Earth,……Earth rallied……destroyed Evil--with……help of heroes."</p><p>“那是个谎言！”她擦了擦嘴，仿佛要将刚刚听到的东西从嘴边抹去。“你提到的那个名字绝对不可再提，它只能指邪恶之地，它是邪恶的源头。在邪恶之地与其姐妹世界登场之前，地球一直是独一无二的。邪恶之地几乎毁灭了地球，但是地球最后团结起来，借着一些英雄的帮助，终于摧毁了邪恶之地。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Earth……before this Evil.……you sure of that?"</p><p>“地球的历史早于这个邪恶之地，这点你确定吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Long before. Earth……alone in……Galaxy……thousands of years--millions of years."</p><p>“早得太多了。地球曾在银河系独处了数万年——乃至数百万年。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Millions of years? Humanity existed on it……millions of years with no other people on……other world?"</p><p>“数百万年？人类在其上生存了数百万年，当时其他的世界都没有人？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Thats true. Thats true. Thats true."</p><p>“那是事实，那是事实，那是事实！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"But……do……know……this? Is it……in a computer program? Or a printout? Do……have anything I……read?"</p><p>“但你又是如何知道这些的？这些都在一个电脑程序里吗？或是在一份列印表中？你有任何东西能让我读一读吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Mother Rittah shook……head. "I heard……old stories from my mother,……heard it from hers,……so on……back. I have no children, so I tell……stories to others,……it……come to an end. This is a time of disbelief."</p><p>瑞塔嬷嬷摇了摇头。“我从母亲那里听来这些古老的故事，她又是从她的母亲那里听来的，就是这样一脉相传。我没有子女，所以我把这些故事说给别人听。但它仍有可能就此失传，这是个失去信仰的时代。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Not really, Mother. There……people……speculate about prehistoric times……who study some of……tales of lost worlds."</p><p>铎丝说：“嬷嬷，这很难讲。还是有人推论史前时代的种种可能，并且研究那些失落世界的相关传说。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Mother Rittah made a motion of……arm as though to wipe it away. "They look at it with cold eyes. Scholarly. They……to……it in with their notions. I could tell……stories……a year of……great hero Ba-Lee,……you would have no time to listen……I have lost……strength to tell."</p><p>瑞塔嬷嬷伸出手臂做了一个动作，仿佛是要扫开那句话。“他们用冷眼面对这个问题。那是学术，他们试图将它融入既有的概念。有关大英雄笆雳的故事，我可以跟你说上一年，可是你不会有那么多时间听，我也没有那么多精力讲。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, "Have……ever heard of robots?"</p><p>谢顿道：“你听说过机仆吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>The……woman shuddered……her voice……almost a scream. "Why do……ask such things? Those were artificial human beings, evil in themselves……the work of……Evil worlds. They were destroyed……should never be mentioned."</p><p>老妇人突然抖了一下，她的声音则几乎变作尖叫。“你、为、何、要、问、这、种、事？那种东西是人工的人类，是那些邪恶世界的产物，本身就是一种邪恶。它们早就遭到毁灭，再也不该提起。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"There……one special robot, wasnt there, that……Evil worlds hated?"</p><p>“有一个特殊的机仆，是那些邪恶世界憎恨的对象，对不对？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Mother Rittah tottered toward Seldon……peered into……eyes. He could feel……hot breath on……face. "Have……come to mock……You know of these things……yet……ask?……do……ask?"</p><p>瑞塔嬷嬷蹒跚地走向谢顿，紧紧盯着他的双眼。他甚至感觉得到她的热气喷在自己脸上。“你是专门来愚弄我的吗？你已经知道这些事，还偏偏要问？你为什么要问？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Because I wish to know."</p><p>“因为我希望知道。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"There……an artificial human being……helped Earth. He……Da-Nee, friend of Ba-Lee. He never died……lives somewhere, waiting……his time to return. None knows when that time Will……but someday he Will come……restore……great……days……remove……cruelty, injustice,……misery. That is……promise."</p><p>“曾有一个人工的人类帮助过地球。他名叫答霓，是笆雳的朋友。他从来没死，一直活在某个角落，等待着他的时代重返。没有人知道会是什么时候，不过总有一天他会回来，来复兴那个伟大的古老时代，并除去所有的残酷、不义和悲惨。那是他的承诺。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>At this,……closed……eyes……smiled, as if remembering ...</p><p>说到这里，她闭上眼睛，露出微笑，好像回想起……</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon waited a while in silence, then sighed……said, "Thank you, Mother Rittah.……have been very helpful. What is your fee?"</p><p>谢顿默默等了一会儿，然后叹了一口气。“谢谢你，瑞塔嬷嬷，你对我有很大的帮助。我该付你多少酬劳？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"So pleasant to meet Outworlders,"……old woman replied. "Ten credits.……I offer……some refreshment?"</p><p>“很高兴能遇见外星人士。”老妇人答道，“十个信用点。我有荣幸招待你们一些茶点吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No, thank you," said Seldon earnestly. "Please take twenty.……need only tell us……to……back to……Expressway from here.--And, Mother Rittah, if……can arrange to have some of your tales of Earth……into a computer disc, I Will……you well."</p><p>“不用了，谢谢你。”谢顿一本正经地说，“请收下二十点。你只要告诉我们怎样从这里回到捷运站。还有，瑞塔嬷嬷，如果你能把有关地球的传说录进电脑磁片，我会付你很好的价钱。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I would need so much strength.……well?"</p><p>“我需要花很多力气。价钱有多好？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"It would depend on……long……story is……how well it is told. I might……a thousand credits."</p><p>“那要看故事有多长，以及说得有多好。我也许会付一千点。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Mother Rittah licked……lips. "A thousand credits?……how Will I find……when……story is told?"</p><p>瑞塔嬷嬷舔了舔嘴唇。“一千点？可是故事录好之后，我要怎样找到你？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I Will give……the computer code number at which I……be reached."</p><p>“我会给你一个电脑址码，这样就能联络到我。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>After Seldon gave Mother Rittah……code number, he……Dors left, thankful……the comparatively clean odor of……alley outside. They walked briskly in……direction indicated by……old woman.</p><p>谢顿将址码写给瑞塔嬷嬷后，便与铎丝一同离去。相较之下，外面巷道的空气简直清新宜人。他们根据老妇人的指引，踏着轻快的步伐向前走去。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "That wasnt a very long interview, Hari."</p><p>铎丝说：“哈里，这并不是一次很长的晤谈。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I know.……surroundings were terribly unpleasant……I felt I……learned enough. Amazing……these folktales tend to magnify."</p><p>“我知道。但周遭环境不舒服之至，而且我觉得打听得够多了。真难想象这些民间传说如何放大到这种程度。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"What do……mean, magnify?"</p><p>“你所谓的‘放大’是什么意思？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Well,……Mycogenians fill their Aurora with human beings……lived……centuries……the Dahlites fill their Earth with a humanity that lived……millions of years.……both talk of a robot that lives forever. Still, it makes……think."</p><p>“嗯，麦曲生人将他们的奥罗拉说成上面住有能活好几世纪的人，达尔人则将他们的地球说成有着延续数百万年的人类，而两者都提到一个长生不死的机器人。话说回来，这的确耐人寻味。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"As……as millions of years……theres room for-- Where……we going?"</p><p>“既然有好几百万年，就该有机会——我们正往哪儿走？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Mother Rittah said we go in this direction till we reach a rest area, then follow……sign……CENTRAL WALKWAY, bearing left,……keep on following……sign.……we pass a rest area on……way in?"</p><p>“瑞塔嬷嬷说我们应该沿着这个方向走，直到抵达一个休息区，然后找一个指着左边的‘中央走道’路标，再一直跟着那个路标前进。我们来的时候，有没有经过一个休息区？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"We……be leaving by a route different from……one we came……I don't remember a rest area,……I wasnt watching……route. I……keeping my……on……people we passed and--"</p><p>“我们现在走的这条路，也许和来时的路线不同。我不记得有个休息区，不过刚才我没有注意看路。我的眼睛一直摆在路人身上，而且……”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Her voice died away. Up ahead……alley swelled outward on both sides. </p><p>她的声音逐渐消失。前方的巷道两侧都向外敞开。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon remembered. They……passed that way. There……been a couple of ratty couch pads resting on……walkway floor on either side. </p><p>谢顿想了起来，他们的确曾经路过这里。他还记得两侧的人行道上弃置着一些破烂的沙发垫。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>There was, however, no need……Dors to watch passersby going……as……had coming……There were no passersby.……up ahead in……rest area they spotted a group of men, rather large-sized……Dahlites, mustaches bristling, bare upper arms muscular……glistening under……yellowish indoor light of……walkway. </p><p>然而，铎丝不必再像进来的时候那样防范路人，因为现在一个路人也没有。倒是在前面的休息区里，他们发现有一群人。就达尔人而言，那群人个头相当大，一个个的八字胡都向上竖起。在人行道的昏黄光线照耀下，他们裸露的上臂全都肌肉盘虬，而且熠熠生辉。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Clearly, they were waiting……the Outworlders and, almost automatically, Seldon……Dors came to a halt.……a moment or two,……tableau held. Then Seldon looked behind……hastily.……or three additional……had stepped into view.</p><p>显然，他们是在等待这两位外星人士，谢顿与铎丝几乎自然而然停下脚步。一时之间，双方形成一个静止画面。然后谢顿匆匆向后看了看，发现后面又走出来两三个人。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said between……teeth, "Were trapped. I should……have……you come, Dors."</p><p>谢顿抿着嘴说：“我们落入陷阱了。我不该让你跟来的，铎丝。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"On……contrary. This is……I'm here,……was it worth your seeing Mother Rittah?"</p><p>“刚好相反，这正是我跟来的原因。可是你为了见瑞塔嬷嬷，值得付出这种代价吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"If we……out of this, it was."</p><p>“只要我们能脱身，那就值得。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon then said in a loud……firm voice, "May we pass?"</p><p>然后，谢顿以响亮而坚定的声音说：“我们能过去吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>One of……men ahead stepped forward. He……fully Seldons height of 1.73 meters,……broader in……shoulders……much more muscular. A……flabby at……waist, though, Seldon noted.</p><p>对面的一名男子向前走来。他与身高一米七三的谢顿不相上下，但肩膀比谢顿更宽，而且肌肉更结实。不过，他的腰部有点松垮，谢顿注意到了。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"I'm Marron," he said with self-satisfied significance, as though……name ought to have meaning, "and……here to tell……we don't like Outworlders in……district.……want to come……all right--but if……want to leave, youll have to pay."</p><p>“我叫玛隆，”他以自大自满的口气说，仿佛这个名字应该具有某种意义。“我在这里是要告诉你，我们不喜欢外星人士踏进我们的地盘。你想要进来，可以——但如果要出去，你就得付出代价。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Very well.……much?"</p><p>“很好，多少？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"All youve got.……rich Outworlders have credit tiles, right? Just hand them over."</p><p>“你身上所有的财产。你们阔气的外星人士都有信用瓷卡，对吗？通通交出来。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No."</p><p>“不行。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No point saying……Well just take them."</p><p>“不容你说不行，我们自己会动手。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You cant take them without killing me or hurting me……they wont work without my voiceprint. My normal voiceprint."</p><p>“除非把我打伤或杀掉，否则你休想得到。而且必须配合我的声纹才能使用，我的正常声纹。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Thats……so, Master--see,……being polite--we……take them away from……without hurting……very much."</p><p>“并非如此，老爷——看，我很礼貌——我们可以从你身上取走，却不必把你伤得太厉害。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"How many of……big strong……Will it take? Nine? No." Seldon counted rapidly. "Ten."</p><p>“你们这些粗壮汉子得用上几个？九个？不，”谢顿很快数了一遍，“十个。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Just one. Me."</p><p>“就一个，我。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"With no help?"</p><p>“没有帮手？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Just me."</p><p>“就我一个。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"If……rest of……Will clear away……give us room, I would like to……you……it, Marron."</p><p>“玛隆，如果其他人能闪开，给我们腾出地方，我愿意看看你怎么动手。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You don't have a knife, Master.……want one?"</p><p>“你没有刀子，老爷，你要一把吗？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No,……yours to make……fight even. I'll fight without one."</p><p>“不必，你用你的，这样打斗才算公平。我要赤手空拳上阵。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Marron looked about at……others……said, "Hey, this puny……is a sport. He don't even sound scared. Thats sort of nice. It would be a shame to hurt him. I tell……what, Master. I'll take……girl. If……want me to stop, hand over your credit tile……her tile……use your right voices to activate them. If……say……then after……through with……girl……and thatll take some time"--he laughed--"I'll just have to hurt you."</p><p>玛隆环顾同党众人，然后说：“嘿，这小个子真有种。听他的口气甚至不害怕，这可真不简单。打伤他简直没面子——老爷，我告诉你怎么办。我要对付这姑娘，如果你想要我停手，就把你和她的信用瓷卡一块交出来，再用你们的正确声音启动。如果你说不，那么等我收拾完这姑娘……那可要点时间，”他纵声大笑，“我就不得不伤害你。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"No," said Seldon. "Let……woman……Ive challenged……to a fight--one to one,……with a knife, me without. If……want bigger odds, I'll fight……of you,……let……woman go."</p><p>“不，”谢顿说，“让这女子离去。我已经向你挑战——一对一，你用刀子，我不用。你若想要更大的胜算，我就一个打你们两个，可是先让这名女子离去。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Stop, Hari!" cried……Dors.……he wants……let……come……get……You stay right where……are, Hari,……don't move."</p><p>“哈里，闭嘴！”铎丝叫道，“如果他想要我，就让他过来抓我。你就留在原地，哈里，千万别动。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"You hear that?" said Marron, grinning broadly. "……stay right where……are, Hari,……don't move. I think……little lady wants……You two, keep……still."</p><p>“你们听到了吗？”玛隆咧嘴大笑，“‘你就留在原地，哈里，千万别动。’我说这小妮子想要我。你们两个，把他看牢。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Each of Seldons arms were caught in an iron grip……he felt……sharp point of a knife in……back.</p><p>谢顿的双臂像是被两道铁箍紧紧锁住，他还感到有锐利的刀尖抵在背上。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"Dont move," said a harsh whisper in……ear, "and……can watch.……lady Will probably like……Marrons pretty good at this."</p><p>“别动。”谢顿耳际传来厉声的耳语，“你可以看着。那女的也许会喜欢，玛隆这方面很高明。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors called……again. "Dont move, Hari!"……turned to face Marron watchfully,……half-closed hands poised near……belt.</p><p>铎丝再度叫道：“哈里，别动！”说完，她转身警觉地面对着玛隆，半握的双手挨近腰际的皮带。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He closed in on……purposefully……she waited till he……come within arms length, when suddenly……own arms flashed……Marron found himself facing……large knives.</p><p>他不怀好意地欺近她，而她则不动声色。等到他来到一臂之遥，在她的双臂陡然一闪之后，玛隆便发觉自己面对着两把大刀。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>For a moment, he leaned backward……then he laughed. "The little lady……two knives--knives like……big boys have.……Ive only……one.……thats fair enough."……knife……swiftly out. "I hate to have to……you, little lady, because it Will be more……for both of us if I dont. Maybe I……just knock them……of your hands, huh?"</p><p>一时之间，他猛然向后一仰，然后哈哈大笑。“这小妮子有两把刀——像是大男生用的那种。我却只有一把，不过这也够公平了。”他把刀子迅速亮出来，“我可不愿意失手砍伤你，小妮子，因为如果能避免，我们两个都会获得更多乐趣。也许我把它们从你手上敲掉就好了，啊？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "I don't want to kill you. I'll do……I……to avoid doing……Just……same, I call on……to witness, that if I do kill you, it is to protect my friend, as I am honor-bound to do."</p><p>铎丝说：“我不想杀你，我会尽可能避免那样做。话说回来，我要求大家做个见证，万一我真杀了你，那是为了保护我的朋友，是我责无旁贷。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Marron pretended to be terrified. "Oh, please don't kill……little lady." Then he burst into laughter……was joined by……other Dahlites present. </p><p>玛隆装出害怕的样子。“喔，小妮子，求求你别杀我。”说完他立刻哈哈大笑，在场的达尔人也跟着笑起来。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Marron lunged with……knife, quite wide of……mark. He tried it again, then a third time,……Dors never budged.……made no attempt to fend……any motion that……not truly aimed at her.</p><p>玛隆举刀向前刺出，落点却离铎丝相当远。接着他又试了第二次、第三次，但铎丝始终一动不动。对于并非真正瞄准她的攻击，她根本不试图格挡。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Marrons expression darkened. He……trying to make……respond with panic,……he……only making himself seem ineffectual.……next lunge……directly at……and Dorss left-hand blade moved flashingly……caught……with a force that pushed……arm aside.……right-hand blade flashed inward……made a diagonal slit in……T-shirt. A thin bloody line smeared……dark-haired skin beneath. Marron looked down at himself in shock as……onlookers gasped in surprise.</p><p>玛隆的表情转趋阴沉。他本想让她惊慌失措，不料弄巧成拙，只是令自己显得徒劳无功。于是，下一次的攻击便直接瞄准她。铎丝的左手刀随即闪电般挥出，猛力迎向他的武器，将他的手臂震开。她的右手刀则迅疾内转，在他的短衫上划出一道对角线。短衫底下长满黑色胸毛的皮肤，立时绽出一条细微的血痕。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon felt……grip on……weaken slightly as……two……held……were distracted by a duel……going quite as they……expected. He tensed himself.</p><p>玛隆在震撼中低头望向自己，围观的众人则在惊讶中喘不过气来。谢顿觉得抓着自己的两个人放松了点，这场决斗并未完全按照他们的预期进行，因而吸引了他们的注意力。谢顿暗自蓄势待发。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Now Marron lunged again……this time……left hand shot outward to enclose Dorss right wrist. Again Dorss left-hand blade caught……knife……held it motionless, while……right hand twisted agilely……drew downward, even as Marrons left hand closed upon……It closed on nothing……the blade……when he opened……hand there……a bloody line down……palm.</p><p>此时玛隆再度举刀进攻，这回他的左手同时出击，朝铎丝的右腕抓去。铎丝的左手刀再度格住他的利刃，令它一时动弹不得；她的右手做了一个敏捷的回旋，在玛隆的左手挨近的当儿向下一沉。结果，除了刀刃他什么也没抓到，而当他张开手的时候，手掌上赫然出现一道血痕。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors sprang back……Marron, aware of……blood on……chest……hand, roared……chokingly, "Someone toss me another knife!" </p><p>铎丝立即向后跳开。玛隆在发觉胸部与手掌挂彩后，以透不过气的声音咆哮道：“哪个人再扔给我一把刀！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>There……hesitation……then……of……onlookers tossed……own knife underhanded. Marron reached……it,……Dors……quicker.……right-hand blade struck……thrown knife……sent it flying backward, whirling as it went.</p><p>一阵迟疑之后，一名同党将自己的刀偷偷抛过去。玛隆正要伸手去接，铎丝的行动却比他更快。她的右手刀击向那把掷出的利刃，让它循着原路一面打转一面飞回去。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon felt……grips on……arms weaken further. He lifted them suddenly, pushing up……forward,……was free.……two captors turned toward……with a sudden shout,……he quickly kneed……in……groin……elbowed……other in……solar plexus……both went down.</p><p>谢顿感到两只手臂上的抓力变得更弱。他猛然举起双臂，用力向前推，立刻就重获自由。抓他的两个人大叫一声，转过身来面对着他，他则以膝头迅速撞向其中一人的鼠蹊，并用手肘击向另一人的胃部，两人随即应声倒地。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He knelt to draw……knives of each……rose as double-armed as Dors. Unlike Dors, Seldon……not know……to handle……blades,……he knew……Dahlites would scarcely be aware of that.</p><p>他跪下去拔取那两人身上的佩刀，起身之后，他就和铎丝一样成为双刀客。然而与铎丝不同的是，谢顿不会使用这种武器，但他知道那些达尔人几乎不可能发觉。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors said, "Just keep them off, Hari. don't attack yet.--Marron, my next stroke Will……be a scratch."</p><p>铎丝说：“别让他们靠近就行，哈里，暂时还别攻击——玛隆，我的下一击将不只是皮肉伤。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Marron, totally enraged, roared incoherently……charged blindly, attempting by sheer kinetic energy to overwhelm……opponent. Dors, dipping……sidestepping, ducked under……right arm, kicked……foot against……right ankle,……down he crashed,……knife flying.</p><p>玛隆陷入极度的愤怒，一面发出毫无意义的咆哮，一面展开盲目的攻击，试图单用巨大的冲力压倒对手。铎丝身形一沉，向旁边跨出一步，同时低头避开他的右臂，并在他的右脚踝踢了一记。玛隆立刻瘫倒在地，手中的刀飞了出去。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She then knelt, placed……blade against……back of……neck……the other against……throat,……said, "Yield!"</p><p>然后她跪在地上，将一把刀架在他的后颈，另一把抵住他的咽喉，说道：“投降！”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>With another yell, Marron struck……against……with……arm, pushed……to……side, then scrambled to……feet.</p><p>大吼一声之后，玛隆重新发动攻势。他用一只手推开她，然后挣扎着站起来。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>He……not……stood up completely when……was upon him,……knife slashing downward……hacking away a section of……mustache. This time he yowled like a large animal in agony, clapping……hand to……face. When he drew it away, it……dripping blood.</p><p>当她再度欺近时，他尚未完全站稳。只见一刀砍下去，便将他的八字胡削去一截。这次他像一头重伤的巨兽般发出哀号，还一巴掌拍向自己的脸部。当他将手拿开时，那只手正滴着鲜血。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors shouted,……wont grow again, Marron. Some of……lip went with……Attack once more……youre dead meat."</p><p>铎丝喊道：“它不会再长出来，玛隆，有一片嘴唇跟它一起飞了。再做一次攻击，你就是一具死尸。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She waited,……Marron……had enough. He stumbled away, moaning, leaving a trail of blood.</p><p>她严阵以待，但玛隆已经吃不消了。他一面呻吟，一面跌跌撞撞逃了开，沿途还留下一条血迹。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors turned toward……others.……two that Seldon……knocked down were still lying there, unarmed……not anxious to……up.……bent down,……their belts with……of……knives……then slit their trousers. </p><p>铎丝转身面向其他人。被谢顿打倒的那两个还躺在那里，他们已被缴械，并未急着爬起来。她弯下腰，用一把刀切断他们的皮带，又划开他们的裤子。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>"This way, youll have to hold your pants up when……walk,"……said. </p><p>“这样一来，你们就得提着裤子走路。”她说。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She stared at……seven……still on their feet,……were watching……with awestruck fascination. "And which of……threw……knife?"</p><p>她又瞪着仍然站在原处的七个人，他们都以敬畏的眼神如痴如醉地望着她。“刚才扔刀子的，是你们哪一个？”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>There……silence.</p><p>众人一片沉默。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She said,……doesnt matter to……Come……at a time or……together,……each time I slash, someone dies."</p><p>她又说：“对我而言没有差别。一个一个来或一起上都行，但我每砍一刀，就会去掉一条命。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>And with……accord,……seven turned……scurried away.</p><p>七个人动作一致地急忙转身，拔腿逃命去了。</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p> Dors lifted……eyebrows……said to Seldon, "This time, at least, Hummin cant complain that I failed to protect you."</p><p>铎丝扬起眉毛，对谢顿说：“至少这一次，夫铭不能怪我没尽到保护你的责任。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Seldon said, "I still cant believe what I saw. I didnt know……could do anything like that--or talk like that either."</p><p>谢顿说：“我仍然无法相信眼前的一切。我一直不知道你能做这样的事——或是能说这样的话。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>Dors merely smiled. "You have your talents too. We make a good pair. Here, retract your knife blades……put them into your pouch. I think……news Will spread with enormous speed……we……get……of Billibotton without fear of being stopped."</p><p>铎丝只是微微一笑。“你也有你的本事，我们是一对好搭档。来，让手中的刀子回鞘，再放进你的袋囊。我想消息会以极高的速度流传，因此我们可以顺利离开脐眼，不必担心再被拦住去路。”</p></div>
<div class='layout'><p>She……quite right.</p><p>她说得相当正确。</p></div>

